 PORTSMOUTH, Dec. 9, 2021 (Xinhua) --   A yellow warning for wind has been issued in Britain Tuesday as storm Barra has brought strong winds, heavy rain and snow to parts of the country. Storm Barra came just 10 days after Storm Arwen caused disruption and three fatalities across Britain. British Prime Minister Boris Johnson said Tuesday that the country must "learn the lessons for the future" and prepare for more storms as damaging as Arwen and Barra.  Photo taken on Dec. 8, 2021 shows flooding in a park next to the seafront following storm Barra in Portsmouth, Britain. (Photo by Tim Ireland/Xinhua)  Waves hit the sea wall in New Brighton, Britain, Dec. 8, 2021. (Photo by Jon Super/Xinhua)  A tree falls down following storm Barra in Aberdeen, Scotland, Britain, Dec. 8, 2021. (Photo by Liu Ning/Xinhua)  Children play on a fallen tree following storm Barra in Aberdeen, Scotland, Britain, Dec. 8, 2021. (Photo by Liu Ning/Xinhua)  A tree falls down following storm Barra in Aberdeen, Scotland, Britain, Dec. 8, 2021. (Xinhua)  Vehicles drive through puddle in Manchester, Britain, Dec. 8, 2021. (Photo by Jon Super/Xinhua)  Waves hit the sea wall in New Brighton, Britain, Dec. 8, 2021. (Photo by Jon Super/Xinhua)  Photo taken on Dec. 8, 2021 shows damage to the seafront following storm Barra in Portsmouth, Britain. (Photo by Tim Ireland/Xinhua)  Vehicles drive through puddle in Manchester, Britain, Dec. 8, 2021. (Photo by Jon Super/Xinhua)  Photo taken on Dec. 8, 2021 shows road closure signs at the seafront following storm Barra in Portsmouth, Britain. (Photo by Tim Ireland/Xinhua)  A child plays on a fallen tree following storm Barra in Aberdeen, Scotland, Britain, Dec. 8, 2021. (Photo by Liu Ning/Xinhua)  Produced by Xinhua Global Serviceâ– 